---
title: Chris Collins – Full Stack Developer & Digital Designer based in Glasgow
description: Chris Collins is a Full Stack Developer & Digital Designer based in Glasgow, Scotland.
layout: base.njk

pagination:
    data: collections.log
    size: 100
    alias: log
---

<div class="container md:my-8">
    <div class="lg:flex items-center justify-between lg:text-center mb-8">
        <section class="max-w-xl mx-auto">
            <h1 class="text-xl md:text-3xl text-gray-600 dark-mode:text-gray-400 mb-1 leading-tight">Hello, I’m Chris</h1>
            <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl leading-tight mb-4 md:mb-6 font-bold">I design and build digital products, hike and take photos.</h2>
            <p class="text-lg md:text-xl sans-serif max-w-xl">I'm a Full Stack Developer & Digital Designer based in Glasgow, Scotland. At present I'm building web things at <a href="https://news.stv.tv" rel="noreferrer" class="cool-link" target="_blank">STV News</a>.</p>
        </section>
    </div>

    <section class="flex justify-between items-center my-8">
        <h2 class="text-xl leading-tight font-semibold">Latest Walk Reports</h2>
        <a href="/log">View all</a>
    </section>

    <ul class="flex -mx-6 scroll-snap scrolling-touch overflow-x-scroll">
        {% for hike in log %}
            {% if hike.url %}
                <li class="scroll-snap-child py-3 px-6 w-9/12 md:w-1/2 lg:w-1/3 flex-none overflow-hidden" style="min-width: 290px;">
                    <a class="no-underline h-full rounded overflow-hidden block mb-4" href="{{ hike.url | url }}">
                        <img class="rounded-lg" src="{{ hike.url | url }}{{ hike.data.featured_image }}">
                        <div class="h-full flex-col">
                            <span class="text-xs leading-none opacity-50 font-bold">{{ hike.data.date | simpleDate }}</span>
                            <h5 class="font-semibold leading-snug md:text-xl">{{ hike.data.name }}</h5>
                        </div>
                    </a>
                </li>
            {% endif %}
        {% endfor %}
    </ul>
</div>